<br>
I am from a fairly small guild.  One that is definately not planes capable.  To put a stop to open raids would mean an end for small family oriented guilds in my opinion.  <br>
<br>
I went on my first plane raid two weeks ago with Sterm.  He holds a good raid.  I like his loot rules and the way he takes control.  The week after my first plane raid I went with him again and invited a few more people from my guild to come along who have never been on a plane raid before.  They had a great time.<br>
<br>
Anyway my point is that the two times I went with Sterm the majority of the people who went were different on the two different occasions.  Sterm doesn't have to hold the open raids if he doesn't want to and as you all know it does require a lot of effort to organise a plane raid.  Especially when the majority of people who go have never grouped before and are not used to each other's abilities.  To cut off the weekly raids is wrong in my opinion.  Mily and Sterm and whoever else holds these raids...  I salute you...  for giving the people in smaller guilds and unguilded people the chance to get up there and have a chance at some planar loot.<br>
<br>
I would be greatly disappointed if this had to stop.<br>
<br>
Everquest is not only about the guilds... its about the people. <p><BR>
