<br>
A suggestion I would make is maybe don't allow open raids to post out so far in advance. With the other limitations (3 raid limit) and so forth, this would allow for guilds who can organize ahead of time to make a reservation while we still kinda have pickup raids in between. Maybe say you can't post a open raid more than 7 days before the intended date, there by allowing yourself enough time to coordinate, allows the guilds to still get in on the action, and doesn't clutter the board up too much. I think we all understand the purpose of open raids is to allow players without the proper guild backing to check out the Planes. <br>
