<br>
It gives those with small and/or no guild affiliations the opportunity to get to the planes and experience the reward of a large-scale raid working in cooperation with many other people.  It also gives them the chance for a bit of upgraded loot they would never have the chance to get otherwise.<br>
<br>
On Luclin we have fought hard to hammer out a reservation system to accomodate and assist not only the larger uber-guilds in determining dates for their raids, but also for small guilds or independent individuals.  I think for the most part (there are a few flaws) we have done a good job in coming up with a fair system. <br>
<br>
If one person takes it into his or her mind, he could easily &quot;work the system&quot; by posting reservations as an open raid to benefit his guild - perhaps hoping that by posting dates in addition to the dates his guild has the plane reserved he will have additional opportunity to slay the Gods and benefit his guild's Epic Quest endeavors or perhaps he just want to get his guild outfitted in planar gear more quickly.<br>
<br>
I believe this is the situation Valas is addressing by making this post and I think it is a valid one.<br>
<br>
Milynna seems to be an honest person and I do not think she would try to work the system to her or Apex's advantage and I would hope that she's working diligently to assure Apex is kept apart from these open raids..... but who can be sure that some other less honest person wouldn't do the opposite?<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Odomora<br>
